absorbed-dose-equivalent.description: The radiation absorbed by a fixed mass of biological tissue.

absorbed-dose-rate.description: The absorbed dose of ionizing radiation imparted at a given location per unit of time (second, minute, hour, or day).

absorbed-dose.description: The energy deposited in a medium by ionizing radiation per unit mass.

activity.description: The time spent on a given activity (tasks, sports, etc.).

plain.description: Plain activity event with no specific content; the activity is defined by the event's stream, time and duration, and possibly description and tags.

angle.description: The figure formed by two rays.

angular-acceleration.description: The rate of change of angular velocity.

area.description: The extent of a two-dimensional surface or shape, or planar lamina, in the plane.

attributes.description: To record attributes, such as blood type, date of birth or skin type.

biological-sex.description: An attribute type for the user’s sex

blood-type.description: An attribute type for the user’s blood type

skin-type.description: An attribute type for the user’s skin type

audio.description: To record audio (conversations, voice messages, etc.).

attached.description:
The audio source is the file attached to the event (no explicit content defined).
You can use the event's duration to mirror the recording's duration.

url.description: A reference to an audio file online.

frequency.description: The frequency tested in the hearing test. Unit: hz

leftEarSensitivity.description: The sensitivity of the left ear. Unit: dB

rightEarSensitivity.description: The sensitivity of the right ear. Unit: dB

start.description: The start date for the sample. Unit: date in ISO 8601 format

end.description: The end date for the sample. Unit: date in ISO 8601 format

ip.description: The IP address of the source, if any
The IP address of the source, if any

blood-pressure.description: To record a blood pressure measurement.

mmhg-bpm.description: The blood pressure measurement. Pressures are stored in mmHg and the heart rate in bpm

boolean.description: To record whether an attribute is true, e.g. if the user has a wheelchair.

bool.description: An attribute type for true or false

call.description: To record references to phone calls (landline, mobile, Skype, etc.).

name.description: The contact's name (or a free-form identifier)

capacitance.description: The ability of a body to store an electrical charge.

catalytic-activity.description: The  increase in rate of a chemical reaction due to the participation of a substance called a catalyst.

clinical.description: The clinical record stores information about a single condition, procedure, or result, along with a fhir resource underlying data from the user’s healthcare institution.

fhir.description: Type to record the clinical information, including an attachment, corresponding to the data of the fhir resource.

displayName.description: The primary display name of the clinical record.

clinicalType.description: An identifier that indicates the type of record, such as allergy or condition record.

fhir.description: The Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources (FHIR) data for this record.

identifier.description: The value from the FHIR resource’s id field.

contact.description: To record events related to people (meeting someone special, business encounters, etc.).

facebook.description: A Facebook user as specified in the Graph API: https://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/api/user/

vcard.description: A business card in vCard 2.0-3.x format. See: rfc2425, rfc2426.

count.description: To record the counting of objects (eggs, apples, etc.).

generic.description: For general items that demand no particular handling.

credentials.description: To record credentials, such as secret keys, passwords or access rights.

pryv-api-endpoint.description: Necessary information to access a Pryv.io account. Url in the format of http(s)://{token}@{apiEndpoint}

data-quantity.description: Unit of information in computing and digital communications.

date.description: To record a date and time.

density.description: The density of a material (volumetric mass density).

dynamic-viscosity.description: The resistance to flow of a fluid under an applied force.

electric-charge-line-density.description: The electric charge per unit volume of space, in one, two or three dimensions.

electric-charge.description: The electric charge of an object.

electrical-conductivity.description: A material that accommodates the transport of electric charge.

electromotive-force.description: Voltage generated by a battery or by the magnetic force.

encrypted.description: For client-side-encrypted events. The decrypted payload is expected to be a JSON object with the regular type and content properties (e.g. { "type": "..", "content": ".." }). If the event has attached files, they are expected to be similarly encrypted.

aes-text-base64.description: AES encrypted payload, with a text key and a Base64 payload.

keyRef.description: A reference (e.g. id, name in keychain) to the key to use for decryption.

hint.description: Alternative to keyRef. A textual hint about which key to use for decryption.

energy.description: The capacity of a physical system to perform work.

file.description: To record a file, or a group of files. A fallback type for data with no specific handling in Pryv.

attached.description: The file is attached to the event

attached-multiple.description: A set of file attached. Structure can be declared in the filenames.

url.description: A reference to a file hosted elsewhere

force.description: A push or pull upon an object resulting from the object's interaction with another object.

frequency.description: The number of occurrences of a repeating event per unit time.

hz.description: Hertz (also known as cycles per second)

linear-acceleration.description: The rate of change of linear velocity.

luminous-intensity.description: The wavelength-weighted power emitted by a light source.

message.description: To record messages, such as e-mails or posts on social networks.

facebook.description: A Facebook post. See [Facebook's API docs](https://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/api/post/) for reference. Facebook properties `message` and `created_time` map to event `description` and `time` respectively. Facebook attached pictures can be directly mapped to attachments. Other Facebook properties such as `link`, `source`, `privacy` are allowed.

source.description: Either a fully qualified "URL" for an external source or a "filename" for a Flash Movie or Video attached to this event.

properties.description: Relative to `source`: a list of properties for an uploaded video, for example, the length of the video.

picture.description: Either a fully qualified "URL" for an external picture or a "filename" for a picture attached to this event.

status-type.description: One of mobile_status_update, created_note, added_photos, added_video, shared_story, created_group, created_event, wall_post, app_created_story, published_story, tagged_in_photo, approved_friend

twitter.description: A Twitter post. Twitter property `created_at` maps to event `time`. Other Twitter properties (see [Twitter's API docs](https://dev.twitter.com/docs/api/1.1/get/statuses/show/%3Aid)) are allowed.

mol.description: The size of an ensemble of elementary entities, such as atoms, molecules, electrons, and other particles.

money.description: To record sums of money (expenses, loans, stock values, etc.). Format = currency. Based on ISO 4217.

music.description: To record references to music, usualy tracks (from Soundcloud, Shazam tags, etc.).

note.description: To record different kinds of text-based notes, from simple text to more complex formatted content like social network posts.

webclip.description: An HTML-formatted note associated to its source URL.

picture.description: To record any kind of image (photos, designs, screenshots, etc.)

base64.description: The picture is caried in base64 (utf-8) encoded in string

attached.description: The picture is the image file attached to the event (no explicit content defined). TODO: list accepted formats.

url.description: A reference to a picture file online.

wgs84.description: The latest revision of the World Geodetic System (used by GPS).

latitude.description: Unit: degrees north from the equator.

longitude.description: Unit: degrees east from the zero meridian.

horizontalAccuracy.description: The radius of uncertainty for latitude and longitude. Unit: meters. Negative if latitude and longitude are invalid.

verticalAccuracy.description: The radius of uncertainty for altitude. Unit: meters. Negative if altitude is invalid.

speed.description: For informational purposes only. Unit: meters / second. Negative if invalid.

bearing.description: Unit: degrees clockwise from north. Negative if invalid.

power.description: The rate at which energy is transferred, used, or transformed.

pressure.description: The ratio of force to the area over which that force is distributed.

reproductive-health.description: To record reproductive health data, such as menstrual flow or ovulation test results.

sexual-activity.description: A type to record sexual activity

menstrual-flow.description: A type to record the menstrual cycles

mucus-quality.description: A type to record the quality of the mucus

ovulation.description: A type to record the result of an ovulation test

speed.description: The magnitude of the velocity of an object.

symptoms.description: To record medical symptoms, such as abdominal cramps or chest pain.

severity.description: A type to record severity of a symptom such as bloating or abdominal cramps.

appetite-changes.description: A type to represent change in appetite.

time.description: Amount of time. Use with care! To store an activity or duration the "activity/plain" event type is more appropriate, in most cases.

url.description: To record references to online resources. Format ~= protocol.

video.description: To record video (home snippets, Vimeo or YouTube links, etc.).

attached.description: The video is the file attached to the event (no explicit content defined). TODO: list accepted formats.

url.description: A reference to an video file online.

volume.description: The quantity of three-dimensional space enclosed by some closed boundary.

name.fr: Won de la Corée du Nord
